BFN 

  [Text] Chairman Yasir 'Arafat, chairman of the PLO 
Executive Committee and chairman of the Palestinian National 
Authority, issued today a decision requesting all the brothers 
working in the government administrations, institutions, and 
organs in Palestine to remain in their working positions 
according to the decision of the Executive Committee adopted at 
an earlier meeting held this month. 
  Following is the text of the decision: 
  The chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, chairman of the 
Palestinian National Authority, and in accordance with the 
decision of the PLO Executive Committee issued on 4 May 1994, 
the powers accorded him, and the prerequisites of national 
interest, decides the following: 
  1. The brothers working in all government administrations, 
institutions, and organs in Palestine should remain at their 
posts and continue the discharge of their normal duties. 
  2. The National Authority demands the precise and honest 
discharge of all responsibilites laid on our shoulders as a 
whole at this historic period to ensure the proper running of 
the work and in the service of the children of our struggling 
people and militant masses. 
  3. This decision shall be in force from its date and all 
concerned must be informed. 

